Actress Zola Nombona is spreading her wings!The Eastern Cape-born actress told SunBuzz about her latest project, the new series Dancing With The Stars South Africa.The qualified applied theatre practitioner will be seen next year in the dance competition series.Twelve untrained local celebrities will show off their moves with the help of professional Latin and ballroom dancers.Best known for her role as Shado in the second season of Intersexions in 2013, Zola also landed the role of Monde in Mzansi Magic’s Lockdown, of which she has shot two seasons.She recently starred in the series iNumber Number and Love Lives Here.The 25-year-old Zola won last year’s Golden Horn Award for best lead actress for her work in the movie Ingoma.For the dance show, she joins celebrities like TV presenter Thembisa Mdoda, actress Juanita de Villiers and former Miss SA Liesl Laurie.She said the challenge excites her.“I was really excited when I was asked to be part of it,” she said.“It’s something I have never done before. I want to see how far I can go.”Zola told SunBuzz she can dance but has never done ballroom or Latin dancing before.She said she is aiming for the big prize.“I hope I will win and am looking forward to the personal growth that comes from conquering this journey that demands a lot, physically and mentally.”The hosts on the show are radio and TV personality Tracey Lange and Top Billing’s Chris Jaftha.It will kick off on DStv’s channel 101 on 4 February.if(typeof za24_DisplayAd != "undefined") za24_DisplayAd("300x250","2");var viewReq = new Array();function vu(u) {var i=new Image();i.src=u.replace("&amp;","&");viewReq.push(i);}vu("https://securepubads.g.doubleclick.net/pcs/view?xai\x3dAKAOjstjODc1biny42XNt1lGZxroaJ8n-A474DQfXmQZk7XuK5Qp9Zl-QZuLAtvCAfs8X8peTrQtXOhlaonJdsW3f2mtmmmrbYxWH6tj1wYuXkSGMjL1KwHkiWtsF40_FU-_7jjqR7SFZfL1sC6iJp-zAv-TP_5Cu78qgVsilxD8Iu5O9AT1953u8CJ3r8d18DcGStkBMvgXT2OwU-TrQlJt2ktev-8KdnBGBKSsFANebNjrufvVdJqNdVmc76wAJZ7sRxFas0jOJjinn-qih9V5--lK_3yu4CBst